  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Peel and grate the garlic. Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a saucepan set over a medium heat. Add the garlic and fry for 30 seconds until fragrant. Take off the heat and stir through the curry powder."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Finely chop the dried apricots and coriander. Drain and rinse the chickpeas."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add the Greek yoghurt, mayonnaise, mango chutney, chickpeas, flaked almonds, apricots, coriander, and the garlic curry mix to a large bowl. Zest and juice the lemon into the bowl and mix. Season to taste with salt and pepper."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Serve however you fancy. We love this filler sandwiched between with thick slices of sourdough with crisp romaine, a handful of Bombay mix and a scattering of nigella seeds.\n\nIf you're making ahead, pop the filling into the fridge in Tupperware (it will keep for up to 3 days)."
    }
  ],
  "tips": [
    "You can skip the Bombay mix if you want it less crunchy.",
    "Add extra mango chutney for sweetness.",
    "If you're looking for a lighter way to serve you serve in lettuce cups rather than bread."
  ],
